groom (1.1.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * add configuration-reload-on-SIGHUP support
  * make the domain's unavailability HTTP status code configurable (404 by default)
  * do not return transaction ids to clients until requests are forwarded to agents
  * do not log clients requests for disconnected or inactive domains by default
  * use target hostname as Host header in backend requests by default
  * add per-domain configurable POST/PUT body size limit
  * add an option to disable returning the X-Transaction-Id header to clients

 -- Pierre-Yves Kerembellec <py.kerembellec@gmail.com>  Sun, 09 May 2021 19:50:53 +0200

